&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated and enthusiastic person to work within this busy Emergency Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great developmental opportunity for staff within the acute medicine specialty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a very fast paced and highly visual department which provides front line treatment for both Adults and Children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are motivated, have excellent communication and leadership skills and can demonstrate evidence based clinical practice then this is the position for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Comprehensive induction with an initial supernumerary period&lt;br /&gt;- Regular performance review&lt;br /&gt;- A comprehensive education &amp; development programme within the unit &lt;br /&gt;- Access to the Trusts training &amp; development programme&lt;br /&gt;- Management development programme &lt;br /&gt;- Self Rostering &amp; flexible working patterns&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this vacancy will be to cover shift work which will be on a 24/7 basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Clarke / Corrine O&#39;Callaghan-Walker - Lead Nurses - ED&lt;/p&gt;
